{"sectionId":738,"sectionIdLiteral":"738","humanId":"lesson-317","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"I follow in the way appointed me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 317"},"annotation":"W-317","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-317\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"738#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I have a special place to fill; a role for me alone.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Salvation waits until I take this part as what I choose to do.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Until I make this choice, I am the slave of time and human destiny.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>But when I willingly and gladly go the way my Father‚Äôs plan appointed me to go, then will I recognize salvation is already here, already given all my brothers and already mine as well.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"738#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, Your way is what I choose today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Where it would lead me do I choose to go; what it would have me do I choose to do.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Your way is certain, and the end secure.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>The memory of You awaits me there.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"738#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>And all my sorrows end in Your embrace, which You have promised to Your Son, who thought mistakenly that he had wandered from the sure protection of Your loving Arms.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"I have a special place to fill; a role for me alone. Salvation waits until I take this part as what I choose to do. Until I make this choice, I am